.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-3-7::.
4 different games are played: mah-jongg, domino, whist, poker
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: old-henry, tiparillo, bolivar, bongani
The people use 4 different means of transport: tram, airplane, train, bus
 1. the person driving the airplane is on the left or right of the person driving the tram##3
 2. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
 3. the person playing poker is on the left or right of the person driving the airplane##3
 4. the bolivar-smoker is on the right of the person driving the train##1
 5. the person driving the train is on the left of the person playing domino##1
 6. the person playing whist is the person playing whist##1
 7. the bolivar-smoker is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1
 8. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the bongani-smoker##3
 9. the person driving the tram is on the right of the person playing domino##1
10. the tiparillo-smoker is on the left or right of the bolivar-smoker##3
11. the tiparillo-smoker is the person driving the train##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1       |    2     |     3     |     4     |
| Game         | whist    | mah-jongg  | domino | poker   |
| Cigar           | bongani | tiparillo   | bolivar    | old-henry |
| Transport   | bus      | train | airplane | tram  |

